body:
@mrry - Thanks.  I agree this is very unlikely.

@abhijayghildyal  After taking a look at the training program, I'm now wondering if this is something to do with the use of `tf.train.replica_device_setter` ?

In particular, you are using parameter servers, but when you call this method you do not make any mention of `ps_tasks`.  If you read the [documentation](https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.10/api_docs/python/train.html#replica_device_setter) you will see that `ps_tasks` defaults to zero, but you probably need to set it to 1 or pass in your `cluster_spec`.

I can't immediately think how this would go wrong, but it seems like this is worth fixing before spending time on the other problem.
